18/10/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- James Franklin Jeffrey, the new US ambassador to Albania, arrived in Tirana Thursday (17 October). 
He takes over from interim Ambassador Elisabeth Shelton, who was appointed following the death of Joseph Limprecht several months ago. 
Prior to his appointment, Jeffrey worked as deputy chief of the US mission in Ankara.
In other news, a border checkpoint opened Wednesday between Kosovo and Albania. 
The crossing is at the village of Shishtavec, in the Kukes district. 
(ATA, Albanian News - 18/10/02)
